<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5284&amp;p=47791#p47791"><![CDATA[
Well, it's impossible for the MMC3 to stop the NES' CPU. All it does its bankswitching PRG and CHR high adress, and generating IRQs.<br />It should have bankswiched the wrong PRG bank or something like that for it "not to run".<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Mon Jun 08, 2009 8:18 am</p><hr />
