<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5284&amp;p=47747#p47747"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Difference between MMC3 revisions]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5284&amp;p=47747#p47747"><![CDATA[
There is no known difference yet (according to the wiki), but the game may require proper data to be in the CHR-ROM for whathever reason (security checks, sprite zero hits or just data stored here) so it's a good idea to always keep your CHR-ROM in sync with the corresponding PRG-ROM when reprogramming your EPROMs.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sun Jun 07, 2009 10:06 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
